<title>BRAZIL: Brazil FGV to rate firms in '97, in talks with S&amp;P.</title>
<headline>Brazil FGV to rate firms in '97, in talks with S&amp;P.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1996-12-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazil's private Getulio Vargas Foundation (FGV) plans to start rating Brazilian companies next year and is speaking with U.S. rating firm Standard &amp; Poors about forming a partnership, an official said.</p>
<p>&quot;We are just exchanging ideas which could lead to a possible venture in the future. But nothing has been formalized yet,&quot; Sergio da Costa, head of FGV's business studies department, told Reuters.</p>
<p>Costa said FGV plans to start rating Brazilian companies on its own in the first half 1997, noting FGV would focus its ratings on Brazilian companies issuing papers in the domestic market.</p>
<p>Recently, Duff &amp; Phelps set up a partnership with Brazil's SR Rating to rate Brazilian firms.</p>
<p>-- Romina Nicaretta, Sao Paulo newsroom, 5511 248 5415</p>
